ection":14,"text":"Or maybe Wernicke-Korsakoff syndrome?","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031516,0.066711,0.078873,0.08898,0.096678,0.10028,0.10231,0.10066,0.095226,0.092843,0.080292,0.065641],"unified_progress":[0.037435,0.064872,0.081661,0.092996,0.098016,0.10485,0.10322,0.10187,0.096708,0.09083,0.074552,0.052996]},{"section":15,"text":"But that's more about memory issues, ophthalmoplegia, ataxia.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025756,0.060306,0.075652,0.088153,0.097321,0.10189,0.10676,0.10389,0.097848,0.096919,0.082565,0.062933],"unified_progress":[0.030527,0.059304,0.078713,0.089475,0.098653,0.10504,0.10519,0.10589,0.10109,0.10001,0.076175,0.04993]},{"section":16,"text":"He doesn't have those here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025026,0.059025,0.073945,0.082911,0.089814,0.095353,0.10246,0.10525,0.10431,0.10021,0.092642,0.069043],"unified_progress":[0.030798,0.061873,0.075764,0.084883,0.093976,0.095261,0.10103,0.10463,0.10281,0.11008,0.084788,0.054111]},{"section":17,"text":"The key points are the recent alcohol cessation, acute onset of mental status changes, disorientation, and visual hallucinations.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037583,0.072599,0.077583,0.080336,0.084846,0.089488,0.092394,0.094405,0.09495,0.095775,0.094316,0.085725],"unified_progress":[0.045589,0.068418,0.073942,0.079937,0.086321,0.092856,0.096453,0.09779,0.097819,0.098237,0.090616,0.072021]},{"section":18,"text":"Delirium tremens (DTs) is a severe form of alcohol withdrawal, presenting with confusion, tremors, hallucinations (usually vivid and frightening), autonomic hyperactivity.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033937,0.067483,0.076824,0.086723,0.095042,0.098985,0.10172,0.098183,0.091921,0.090966,0.0816,0.076615],"unified_progress":[0.038602,0.057995,0.075629,0.081618,0.090767,0.10052,0.10075,0.10152,0.098611,0.095883,0.085979,0.072133]},{"section":19,"text":"The disorientation fits with delirium, which is part of DTs.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032978,0.068143,0.081043,0.088745,0.093004,0.093906,0.096323,0.093829,0.090854,0.091847,0.083673,0.085655],"unified_progress":[0.037138,0.057409,0.070289,0.080446,0.086543,0.094088,0.094607,0.097645,0.097778,0.098555,0.095611,0.089891]},{"section":20,"text":"Alternatively, could it be an acute alcoholic hallucinosis?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029179,0.061987,0.07521,0.084369,0.094019,0.097301,0.10092,0.10354,0.10045,0.097568,0.088018,0.067451],"unified_progress":[0.03628,0.066976,0.083341,0.094449,0.096977,0.098134,0.10137,0.10026,0.096606,0.091879,0.077315,0.056421]},{"section":21,"text":"That's a thing too.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024387,0.057399,0.075777,0.086507,0.095329,0.099027,0.10173,0.10156,0.09994,0.096395,0.087101,0.074856],"unified_progress":[0.042044,0.066839,0.08068,0.094882,0.096011,0.096386,0.10028,0.097406,0.093113,0.094251,0.078034,0.060078]},{"section":22,"text":"It can present with clear hallucinations without the confusion or delirium.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030949,0.065275,0.075143,0.084695,0.093307,0.098753,0.10298,0.10144,0.095986,0.094678,0.084372,0.072413],"unified_progress":[0.037677,0.062352,0.076394,0.084088,0.092807,0.10131,0.099852,0.10185,0.098765,0.096969,0.083107,0.06483]},{"section":23,"text":"But in this case, the patient is disoriented, so maybe that's more DTs.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030141,0.061794,0.073715,0.081768,0.08872,0.093331,0.098512,0.10044,0.10001,0.096943,0.092023,0.082597],"unified_progress":[0.03895,0.060525,0.071867,0.081437,0.088263,0.091306,0.095107,0.098968,0.098433,0.10387,0.093011,0.078268]},{"section":24,"text":"Wait, the time frame: three days since last drink.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034266,0.065914,0.075741,0.08257,0.090208,0.096887,0.097053,0.098139,0.097618,0.095316,0.089127,0.07716],"unified_progress":[0.059665,0.083749,0.083528,0.087118,0.088462,0.090272,0.093272,0.092305,0.089162,0.090298,0.079674,0.062496]},{"section":25,"text":"DTs typically occur after 48-72 hours, so that's right on time.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039662,0.071552,0.078198,0.085078,0.091304,0.09631,0.097393,0.096888,0.092678,0.091019,0.083434,0.076486],"unified_progress":[0.071531,0.080182,0.084002,0.086179,0.088492,0.091824,0.089884,0.091368,0.085889,0.084452,0.077202,0.068993]},{"section":26,"text":"The symptoms of disorientation (to time, place, person) and visual illusions/hallucinations are classic for DTs.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040893,0.076109,0.078868,0.082024,0.087422,0.092532,0.094809,0.095779,0.092992,0.09064,0.08687,0.081063],"unified_progress":[0.053412,0.074731,0.081632,0.084116,0.088444,0.094376,0.091822,0.093978,0.091805,0.088947,0.083658,0.07308]},{"section":27,"text":"No focal neurological signs mentioned, so less likely a stroke or head injury.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027621,0.064155,0.078382,0.086463,0.090909,0.094922,0.10027,0.10059,0.10192,0.095576,0.088811,0.070374],"unified_progress":[0.031599,0.064034,0.078892,0.088189,0.096953,0.096757,0.099253,0.10047,0.10072,0.10009,0.083842,0.059197]},{"section":28,"text":"So putting it all together, the most likely diagnosis is delirium tremens.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034288,0.057371,0.062939,0.069152,0.074978,0.079422,0.084862,0.088272,0.092488,0.096384,0.10417,0.15567],"unified_progress":[0.039782,0.040806,0.048604,0.058217,0.063246,0.072342,0.077747,0.086284,0.093328,0.10212,0.13509,0.18244]},{"section":29,"text":"The patient is an alcoholic who stopped drinking three days prior, presenting with acute neuropsychiatric symptoms.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.056032,0.086972,0.07622,0.073534,0.077038,0.083332,0.085007,0.090351,0.089757,0.092424,0.092881,0.096453],"unified_progress":[0.064496,0.065117,0.064723,0.067048,0.073465,0.082002,0.083917,0.093065,0.097191,0.10131,0.10581,0.10186]},{"section":30,"text":"The key features include disorientation (time, place, person), visual illusions, and hallucinations.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045145,0.079693,0.076784,0.075267,0.080175,0.087015,0.089273,0.094244,0.093917,0.09445,0.09616,0.087876],"unified_progress":[0.047581,0.065482,0.06963,0.072473,0.080658,0.0899,0.091584,0.097882,0.10043,0.10199,0.099074,0.083312]},{"section":31,"text":"These symptoms align with alcohol withdrawal delirium, specifically delirium tremens (DTs), which typically occurs 48\u201372 hours after cessation.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037945,0.06572,0.071631,0.07985,0.087281,0.091308,0.095054,0.094128,0.092001,0.093394,0.090309,0.10138],"unified_progress":[0.045004,0.051766,0.066662,0.072655,0.080207,0.090446,0.092746,0.097494,0.098271,0.098242,0.10127,0.10524]},{"section":32,"text":"DTs is characterized by acute confusion, autonomic hyperactivity, and hallucinations/illusions.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033751,0.064274,0.0721,0.081046,0.089943,0.09538,0.099558,0.098178,0.095248,0.095586,0.08927,0.085666],"unified_progress":[0.041223,0.05561,0.069099,0.077154,0.085023,0.095351,0.096185,0.099924,0.10067,0.099966,0.095165,0.08463]},{"section":33,"text":"Other conditions like Wernicke-Korsakoff syndrome are less likely due to the absence of ocular abnormalities or significant ataxia.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027432,0.060286,0.072608,0.082328,0.09028,0.09601,0.1012,0.10109,0.099268,0.097741,0.090707,0.081049],"unified_progress":[0.029862,0.055881,0.071785,0.080785,0.089539,0.095895,0.098675,0.10234,0.10217,0.10383,0.092676,0.07657]},{"section":34,"text":"Acute alcoholic hallucinosis usually lacks the severe confusion and disorientation seen here.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02772,0.059221,0.069984,0.079687,0.088801,0.095211,0.10077,0.1012,0.099229,0.098931,0.093282,0.085959],"unified_progress":[0.032766,0.05557,0.069211,0.078684,0.086964,0.096201,0.097467,0.10197,0.10171,0.10297,0.094768,0.081716]},{"section":35,"text":"The timeline and symptom complex strongly favor DTs.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02596,0.055863,0.069471,0.077222,0.082752,0.086289,0.091448,0.093508,0.097057,0.099967,0.10162,0.11885],"unified_progress":[0.028012,0.046545,0.057187,0.067616,0.07423,0.083929,0.087296,0.094685,0.099946,0.10652,0.11957,0.13446]},{"section":36,"text":"</br> <answer> Delirium tremens </answer>","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036544,0.060787,0.062041,0.066508,0.073231,0.079791,0.0855,0.09009,0.095166,0.097256,0.10554,0.14755],"unified_progress":[0.038561,0.044045,0.050044,0.057079,0.062779,0.073017,0.076397,0.088134,0.096756,0.10435,0.13264,0.1762]}]}}